  "title": "This Couple Got Married on a 60-Foot Water Slide at Wisconsin Dells",
  "script": "Married on a water slide? Jon and Keisha Lakoduk from North Dakota have been traveling the country getting married. 9 times. At 9 different venues. Their latest stop: Wisconsin Dells, where they stood at the top of a 60-foot water slide at Land of Natura Water Park in full wedding gear, said their vows, and went down the slide. Six times in one hour. In the dress. Why? Guinness World Record. They're attempting to break the record for most times a bride has gone down a water slide in a wedding dress. Next stop: a bourbon distillery in Kentucky. They're also attempting world records at every venue. How many weddings is too many weddings?",
